    >[ ] learn to export things to VTODO format $Plans done (commit 4ad774c/43b6e07): plan_to_event -> plan_to_todo, parse_ics_file reads VEVENT+VTODO both. Action-mirror half (action_to_vevent -> action_to_vtodo) deliberately NOT done yet - it shares parse_ics_file/read_ics_dates with reconcile's 3-way sync, so it must land together with reconcile becoming VTODO-aware and a migration path for existing action mirrors, not piecemeal. See caldav-integration/README.md design notes 2026-07-12.$ #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3a974ca12f85
    >[ ] learn to import VTODO $Bigger than the name implies: action_to_vevent -> action_to_vtodo, STATUS mapping (BlockedOrAwaiting -> NEEDS-ACTION plus X-CLEARHEAD-STATUS:blocked), and a migration command rewriting existing action-mirror .ics files as VTODO - these land together as one atomic change. Note: read_ics_dates/parse_ics_file already parse VTODO (component_to_plan is generic) so the read side needs only doc fixes. apply_sync stamps B into the sync store (2026-07-14 design), so the decoupling refactor lands first. See caldav-integration/README.md design notes 2026-07-12 and 2026-07-14.$ #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3abe216ea948
    >[ ] add fields to the sync store ~ $Genericize reconcile() to reconcile<T: PartialEq + Clone> and run it per synced field (state, title, description, due_date), each field an entry in the sync-store map - NOT new _sync columns on Action/ActionMeta (superseded 2026-07-14, see README design notes). Depends on the sync-state decoupling refactor. Independent fields mean one field's conflict doesn't block sync of the others.$ #019f5848-c3bf-7062-a94a-3adcba9847ba
