    >[ ] migrate existing plan .ics files from VEVENT\+RRULE to VTODO\+RRULE $One-time conversion command, not a permanent dual-format read path. Run once after plan_to_event/parse_ics_file switch to VTODO; old VEVENT plan format is retired after conversion. See caldav-integration/README.md design notes 2026-07-12.$ #019f59c4-8c0b-7aa1-88b8-8ec35dee0e2d
    >[ ] extract calendar sync into its own crate $Once VTODO bidirectional sync settles: lift workspace/calendar plus the sync store out of clearhead-core into a separate crate (e.g. clearhead-caldav) depending on core as a library. The contract is the workspace format; core is shared plumbing (parsing, formatting, PendingBatch durability). A fully separate tool writing via the CLI was considered and rejected - TakeCalendar needs atomic batched writes. Mechanical once the domain coupling is gone. See README design notes 2026-07-14.$ #019f5f76-f52a-7251-bd29-28117bf16f47
